cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with logic and formal languages, which suggests it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of probabilistic formalisms also suggests it could belong to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the undecidability result suggests it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
